	<div class="faq-container">
		<h1>Candidate Registration and Party Selection FAQ</h1>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>How does the candidate registration process work in the
				system?</h2>
			<p>Candidates can register themselves by providing necessary
				personal details and selecting a party affiliation from the
				available list during the registration process.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>Can candidates register without affiliating with a political
				party?</h2>
			<p>No, candidates must choose a party affiliation from the list
				provided during registration.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>How are parties and their related information injected into
				candidate profiles?</h2>
			<p>When a candidate selects a party during registration, the
				system automatically injects the party's manifesto and logo
				associated with that specific party into the candidate's profile.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>Are candidates able to modify the party manifesto or logo
				injected into their profile?</h2>
			<p>No, the party manifesto and logo injected into a candidate's
				profile are predetermined and controlled by the system based on the
				selected party during registration.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>What if a candidate wishes to change their affiliated party
				after registration?</h2>
			<p>Once a candidate is registered with a particular party, they
				cannot change their affiliation within the system. It's crucial to
				carefully choose the party during the registration process.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>Is there any specific criteria for parties to be included in
				the available list for candidates to choose from?</h2>
			<p>The list of parties available for candidates to select from is
				predefined and determined by the system administrators or relevant
				authorities managing the election.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>Are there any restrictions on the number of candidates
				affiliated with a particular party?</h2>
			<p>The system does not impose any restrictions on the number of
				candidates affiliated with a specific party. Candidates can freely
				choose from the available party list during registration.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>Can candidates update their profiles after registration,
				apart from the party affiliation?</h2>
			<p>Yes, candidates have the ability to update their profiles,
				including personal information, contact details, and other
				non-party-related information, as needed.</p>
		</div>

	</div>


